<br>
She is located at the entrance to the fear portal.  <br>
<br>
Best strategy for her is to wait for her to cast her damage absorber, and right after that she will cast her pet.  Attack when she starts to cast het pet, cuz she will keep casting it till she succeeds or is interupted.  Either way you have a 8+ second window of free attack.  If you time this right, she wont have much time to cast more than 1 other spell....if that.<br>
<br>
She can, and will try to cast Invoke fear quite often...so have Summon Companion memmed.  Whenever she feared my pet I just summoned him and annulled him.<br>
<br>
She also casts a dd spell, for ~200, a little less tho.<br>
<br>
The way I did it was..send pet when she starts casting hers.  Nuke asap after pet sent it (I used char).  Sit down and med until pet finishes her, pet is feared, or if you feel like nuking 1 more time.<br>
<br>
She has very little hp, too.<br>
<br>
